                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1880: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">William Phillips</persName>,
                        Personal Representative of President Roosevelt in India, to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-24T17:00:00+06:30"
                            >March 24, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>237. Viceroy has expressed his willingness to receive delegation of leaders who
                    recently met in Bombay (reference Ambassador Phillip’s recent telegram from
                        Bombay).<note n="35" xml:id="d228fn35">Telegram No. 173, March 11, <ref
                            target="#pg_208">p. 208</ref>.</note> Competent observers here predict
                    that Viceroy will object [<hi rend="italic">reject?</hi>] leaders request for
                    interview with Gandhi and that such rejection will further accentuate the
                    already intense anti-British feeling in the country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
